{"type":"message","id":"d4f4c86a","parentId":"aa4da13b","timestamp":"2026-04-12T11:48:32.485Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_3db237ef-aedd-4237-8f0c-7ba2c4f873af","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Usage: gog gmail (mail,email) <command> [flags]\nBuild: v0.12.0 (c18c58c)\n\nGmail\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help                   Show context-sensitive help.\n      --color=\"auto\"           Color output: auto|always|never\n  -a, --account=STRING         Account email for API commands\n                               (gmail/calendar/chat/classroom/drive/docs/slides/contacts/tasks/people/sheets/forms/appscript)\n      --client=\"\"              OAuth client name (selects stored credentials +\n                               token bucket)\n      --access-token=STRING    Use provided access token directly (bypasses\n                               stored refresh tokens; token expires in ~1h)\n                               ($GOG_ACCESS_TOKEN)\n      --enable-commands=\"\"     Comma-separated list of enabled top-level\n                               commands (restricts CLI)\n  -j, --json                   Output JSON to stdout (best for scripting)\n  -p, --plain                  Output stable, parseable text to stdout (TSV;\n                               no colors)\n      --results-only           In JSON mode, emit only the primary result (drops\n                               envelope fields like nextPageToken)\n      --select=STRING          In JSON mode, select comma-separated fields\n                               (best-effort; supports dot paths). Desire path:\n                               use --fields for most commands.\n  -n, --dry-run                Do not make changes; print intended actions and\n                               exit successfully\n  -y, --force                  Skip confirmations for destructive commands\n      --no-input               Never prompt; fail instead (useful for CI)\n  -v, --verbose                Enable verbose logging\n      --version                Print version and exit\n\nCommands:\n\nRead\n  search (find,query,ls,list) <query> ... [flags]\n    Search threads using Gmail query syntax\n\n  messages (message,msg,msgs) <command>\n    Message operations\n\n  get (info,show) <messageId> [flags]\n    Get a message (full|metadata|raw)\n\n  attachment <messageId> <attachmentId> [flags]\n    Download a single attachment\n\n  url <threadId> ...\n    Print Gmail web URLs for threads\n\n  history [flags]\n    Gmail history\n\nOrganize\n  thread (threads,read) <command>\n    Thread operations (get, modify)\n\n  labels (label) <command>\n    Label operations\n\n  batch <command>\n    Batch operations\n\n  archive [<messageId> ...] [flags]\n    Archive messages (remove from inbox)\n\n  mark-read (read-messages) [<messageId> ...] [flags]\n    Mark messages as read\n\n  unread (mark-unread) [<messageId> ...] [flags]\n    Mark messages as unread\n\n  trash [<messageId> ...] [flags]\n    Move messages to trash\n\nWrite\n  send [flags]\n    Send an email\n\n  track <command>\n    Email open tracking\n\n  drafts (draft) <command>\n    Draft operations\n\nAdmin\n  settings <command>\n    Settings and admin"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":51,"aggregated":"Usage: gog gmail (mail,email) <command> [flags]\nBuild: v0.12.0 (c18c58c)\n\nGmail\n\nFlags:\n  -h, --help                   Show context-sensitive help.\n      --color=\"auto\"           Color output: auto|always|never\n  -a, --account=STRING         Account email for API commands\n                               (gmail/calendar/chat/classroom/drive/docs/slides/contacts/tasks/people/sheets/forms/appscript)\n      --client=\"\"              OAuth client name (selects stored credentials +\n                               token bucket)\n      --access-token=STRING    Use provided access token directly (bypasses\n                               stored refresh tokens; token expires in ~1h)\n               